rComments: Excellent new professor. The first midterm was unfair in terms of the time given, but the next two exams were much better. Tendency to give out a lot of bonus points which is awesome. Her exam review classes are the best because she goes over a large number of potential (even identical) SA questions on the exams. Easy and interesting class overall.
Learned a lot in her class. If you work hard you can easily do well. Very good prof.

I LOVE HER!!! She is by far the nicest professor I know at uOttawa! She gives really funny examples for hard concepts which are really helpful. Tells you exactly what's going to be in the finals, and is willing to spare alot of her time for her students.  Give her a few more years and she'll be the best econ prof!

Prof. Duangsuda is a nice person, she used some good examples to help students understand the wired concepts pretty well (my opinion), some parts of her lectures might seems challenging, but overall she is still a good choice.
